      "message": "I think pwarn() automatically reads |errno| (because of the %m format string pwarn() uses) but setup_mount_destination() does not always set |errno|. Specifically, the following path does not:\n\n                /* Disallow relative bind mounts. */\n                if (bind) {\n                        warn(\"relative bind-mounts are not allowed: source\u003d%s\",\n                             source);\n                        return -EINVAL;\n                }\n\nThis CL is to support the -EINVAL path.\n\n(If it\u0027s better to fix the -EINVAL path, I\u0027ll do that instead. I mean, errno \u003d EINVAL; return -errno; in setup_mount_destination().)",
